quran[12]{c,v,t,f}:
  37,73,"Then see what was the end of those who were warned (but heeded not)."
  37,74,"Except the chosen slaves of Allâh (faithful, obedient, and true believers of Islâmic Monotheism)."
  37,75,"And indeed Nûh (Noah) invoked Us, and We are the Best of those who answer (the request)."
  38,52,"And beside them will be Qâsirât-at-Tarf [chaste females (wives) restraining their glances (desiring none except their husbands)], (and) of equal ages."
  38,53,"This it is what you (Al-Muttaqûn - the pious - see V.2:2) are promised for the Day of Reckoning!"
  38,54,"(It will be said to them)! Verily, this is Our Provision which will never finish."
  39,37,"And whomsoever Allâh guides, for him there will be no misleader. Is not Allâh All-Mighty, Possessor of Retribution?"
  39,38,"And verily, if you ask them: ",footnotes:1:{39:38} See the footnote of (Verse 12:67).
  39,39,"Say: (O Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم) "
  40,16,"The Day when they will (all) come out, nothing of them will be hidden from Allâh. Whose is the kingdom this Day? (Allâh Himself will reply to His Question): It is Allâh’s the One, the Irresistible!"
  40,17,"This Day shall every person be recompensed for what he earned. This Day no injustice (shall be done to anybody). Truly, Allâh is Swift in reckoning."
  40,18,"And warn them (O Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم) of the Day that is drawing near (i.e. the Day of Resurrection), when the hearts will be choking the throats, and they can neither return them (hearts) to their chests nor can they throw them out. There will be no friend, nor an intercessor for the Zâlimûn (polytheists and wrong-doers), who could be given heed to."